This paper discusses the extraction of tag hierarchies, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL) where tags are used to describe and categorize items. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of tagging systems for photos, films, books, etc., which suggests a connection to information systems (cs.SI) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of recommendation systems, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
